  <title>Pitch Centre Path</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Pitch Centre Path<keyword>Cam Follower Centre</keyword><keyword>Cam Follower Zero Radius</keyword><keyword>Pitch Circle</keyword><keyword>Pitch Path</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:180px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-CamTerminology-pop.ipp" scale="-99.90%" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[2D-Cam and Pitch-Center]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Pitch-Center</text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">&#32;</text><image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption"> -</text> the path, or locus, of the center of a circular <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Roller </text>relative to the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Cam-Part</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text style="font-weight:normal;">When the shape of the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Profile</text><text style="font-weight:bold;">&#32;</text>is not circular, the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Pitch-Center</text> does not have a useful meaning. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Other terms: Pitch-Curve, Pitch-Center-Curve.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-2DCam">2D-Cam dialog</link>&#32;</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
